channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Ferrari 296 GTS Hybrid Review: ‘Arresting, uncanny beauty’ with $366,139 price tag
item.description: As Ferrari rolls toward its first all-electric car, arriving next year, it makes sense that it would also make a hybrid or two.

item.title: Grayson Murray dies at age 30 a day after withdrawing from Colonial, PGA Tour says
item.description: Two-time PGA Tour winner Grayson Murray died Saturday morning at age 30, one day after he withdrew from the Charles Schwab Cup Challenge at Colonial.

item.title: GameStop shares soar on completion of $933 million stock sale after meme frenzy
Janet Yellen warns higher outlook for rates will make it harder to keep deficits and debt expenses under control
item.description: The White House sees 10-year Treasury yields at 3.7% in the early 2030s — almost a full percentage point higher than three years ago.

item.title: Elon Musk plans xAI supercomputer, The Information reports
item.description: Musk founded xAI last year as a challenger to Microsoft-backed OpenAI and Alphabet's Google.

item.title: Buoyed by Nvidia earnings, Wall Street holds hope for a 'Goldilocks scenario'
Could drugs like Ozempic and Wegovy help people live longer? Some experts see them as potential longevity pills
item.description: “The singular most effective and consistent way of extending lifespan in animals is caloric restriction.”

item.title: European banks in Russia face 'awful lot of risk', Yellen says
item.description: President Biden's new secondary sanctions allow the Treasury to cut off banks from the U.S. financial system if they assist Russia's invasion of Ukraine.

item.title: How Morgan Spurlock and ‘Super Size Me’ changed our view of fast food
Tesla shareholders should reject Elon Musk’s ‘excessive’ pay package, proxy advisor says, noting ‘extraordinarily time-consuming projects’ unrelated to EV maker
item.description: “Mr. Musk’s slate of extraordinarily time-consuming projects unrelated to the Company was well-documented before the 2018 grant, and only expanded with his high-profile purchase of the company now known as X,” said Glass Lewis.

item.title: The 'absolute worst' of times for car buying are over
item.description: The “absolute worst” of times for car buying are over as dealerships slash prices heading into the summer, analysts say.

item.title: Nasdaq leads U.S. stocks higher Friday, though Dow snaps 5-week win streak
Top assassin for the Sinaloa drug cartel, once described as ‘a complete psychopath’ with long history of gruesome acts, is extradited to U.S.
item.description: Nestor Isidro Pérez Salas, also known as “El Nini,” is a leader of a group that provided security for the sons of imprisoned drug lord Joaquín “El Chapo” Guzmán, federal investigators said.

item.title: U.S. screens record 2.95 million airline passengers in single day
item.description: The U.S. Transportation Security Administration (TSA) said it screened 2.95 million airline passengers on Friday, the highest number ever on a single day.

item.title: Housing has raised the cost of living — but higher rates aren’t the culprit
